The paper deals with error exponents and moderate deviations in lossless compression, which are topics typically studied in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses constraints on rate pairs and symbol pairs, which are related to coding theory (cs.CC). The use of Taylor series expansions to derive moderate deviations constants suggests a connection to statistical inference (cs.SI). The consideration of blockwise and symbolwise settings may also relate to algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the use of information spectrum-type strong converse suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
